obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (24805)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00013_197452_1517807319869&sectionId=24805&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00013_197452_1517807319869
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Conservation of Foreign`
  line `Exchange and Prevention of Smuggling Activities Act, 1974.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^1`
  line `(being a date not later than the twentieth day of December,`
  line `1974), as the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 19th December, 1974, vide notification No. G.S.R. 690(E), dated 16th December, 1974, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary,`
  line `Part II, sec. 3 (i).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (24806)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00013_197452_1517807319869&sectionId=24806&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00013_197452_1517807319869
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "appropriate Government" means, as respects a detention order made by the Central`
  line `Government or by an officer of the Central Government or a person detained under such order, the`
  line `Central Government, and as respects a detention order made by a State Government or by an officer`
  line `of a State Government or a person detained under such order, the State Government;`
  line
  line `(b) "detention order" means an order made under section 3;`
  line
  line `(c) "foreigner" has the same meaning as in the Foreigners Act, 1946 (31 of 1946);`
  line
  line `(d) "Indian customs waters" has the same meaning as in clause (28) of section 2 of the Customs`
  line `Act, 1962;`
  line
  line `(e) "smuggling" has the same meaning as in clause (39) of section 2 of the Customs Act, 1962`
  line `(52 of 1962), and all its grammatical variations and cognate expressions shall be construed`
  line accordingly;
  line
  line `(f) "State Government", in relation to a Union territory, means the administrator thereof;`
  line
  line `(g) any reference in this Act to a law which is not in force in the State of Jammu and Kashmir`
  line `shall, in relation to that State, be construed as a reference to the corresponding law, if any, in force in`
  line `that State.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (24807)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Power to make orders detaining certain persons.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes `1. The proviso ins. by Act 46 of 1988, s. 15 (w.e.f. 4-7-1988).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00013_197452_1517807319869&sectionId=24807&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00013_197452_1517807319869
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government or the State`
  line `Government or any officer of the Central Government, not below the rank of a Joint Secretary to that Government, specially empowered for the purposes of this section by that Government, or any officer of a`
  line `State Government, not below the rank of a Secretary to that Government, specially empowered for the`
  line `purposes of this section by that Government, may, if satisfied, with respect to any person (including a`
  line `foreigner), that, with a view to preventing him from acting in any manner prejudicial to the conservation`
  line `or augmentation of foreign exchange or with a view to preventing him from--`
  line
  line `(i) smuggling goods, or`
  line
  line `(ii) abetting the smuggling of goods, or`
  line
  line `(iii) engaging in transporting or concealing or keeping smuggled goods, or`
  line
  line `(iv) dealing in smuggled goods otherwise than by engaging in transporting or concealing or`
  line `keeping smuggled goods, or`
  line
  line `(v) harbouring persons engaged in smuggling goods or in abetting the smuggling of goods,`
  line
  line `it is necessary so to do, make an order directing that such person be detained.`
  line
  line `^1[Provided that no order of detention shall be made on any of the grounds specified in this sub-section`
  line `on which an order of detention may be made under section 3 of the Prevention of Illicit Traffic in`
  line `Narcotic Drugs and Psychotropic Substances Act, 1988 or under section 3 of the Jammu and Kashmir`
  line `Prevention of Illicit Traffic in Narcotic Drugs and Psychotropic Substances Ordinance, 1988 (J & K`
  line `Ordinance 1 of 1988).]`
  line
  line `(2) When any order of detention is made by a State Government or by an officer empowered by a`
  line `State Government, the State Government shall, within ten days, forward to the Central Government a`
  line `report in respect of the order.`
  line
  line `(3) For the purposes of clause (5) of article 22 of the Constitution, the communication to a person`
  line `detained in pursuance of a detention order of the grounds on which the order has been made shall be made`
  line `as soon as may be after the detention, but ordinarily not later than five days, and in exceptional`
  line `circumstances and for reasons to be recorded in writing, not later than fifteen days, from the date of`
  line detention.
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (24808)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Execution of detention orders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00013_197452_1517807319869&sectionId=24808&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00013_197452_1517807319869
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `A detention order may be executed at any place in India in the`
  line `manner provided for the execution of warrants of arrest under the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973`
  line `(2 of 1974).`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (24809)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Power to regulate place and conditions of detention.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00013_197452_1517807319869&sectionId=24809&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00013_197452_1517807319869
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `Every person in respect of whom a`
  line `detention order has been made shall be liable--`
  line
  line `(a) to be detained in such place and under such conditions including conditions as to`
  line `maintenance, interviews or communication with others, discipline and punishment for breaches of`
  line `discipline, as the appropriate Government may, by general or special order, specify; and`
  line
  line `(b) to be removed from one place of detention to another place of detention, whether within the`
  line `same State or in another State by order of the appropriate Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that no order shall be made by a State Government under clause (b) for the removal of a`
  line `person from one State to another State except with the consent of the Government of that other State.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5_a:
  sectionId (24810)
  sectionNo 5A
  orderNo 6
  title `Grounds of detention severable.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 35 of 1975, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-7-1975).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00013_197452_1517807319869&sectionId=24810&sectionno=5A&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00013_197452_1517807319869
obj_root_law_sections_5_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[5A. Grounds of detention severable.--Where a person has been detained in pursuance of an order`
  line `of detention under sub-section (1) of section 3 which has been made on two or more grounds, such order`
  line `of detention shall be deemed to have been made separately on each of such grounds and accordingly--`
  line
  line `(a) such order shall not be deemed to be invalid or inoperative merely because one or some of the`
  line `grounds is or are--`
  line
  line `(i) vague,`
  line
  line `(ii) non-existent,`
  line
  line `(iii) not relevant,`
  line
  line `(iv) not connected or not proximately connected with such person, or`
  line
  line `(v) invalid for any other reason whatsoever,`
  line
  line `and it is not, therefore, possible to hold that the Government or officer making such order would have`
  line `been satisfied as provided in sub-section (1) of section 3 with reference to the remaining ground or`
  line `grounds and made the order of detention;`
  line
  line `(b) the Government or officer making the order of detention shall be deemed to have made the`
  line `order of detention under the said sub-section (1) after being satisfied as provided in that sub-section`
  line `with reference to the remaining ground or grounds.]`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (24811)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 7
  title `Detention orders not to be invalid or inoperative on certain grounds.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00013_197452_1517807319869&sectionId=24811&sectionno=6&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00013_197452_1517807319869
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `No detention order shall`
  line `be invalid or inoperative merely by reason--`
  line
  line `(a) that the person to be detained thereunder is outside the limits of the territorial jurisdiction of`
  line `the Government or the officer making the order of detention, or`
  line
  line `(b) that the place of detention of such person is outside the said limits.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (24812)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 8
  title `Powers in relation to absconding persons.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00013_197452_1517807319869&sectionId=24812&sectionno=7&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00013_197452_1517807319869
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the appropriate Government has reason to`
  line `believe that a person in respect of whom a detention order has been made has absconded or is concealing`
  line `himself so that the order cannot be executed, that Government may--`
  line
  line `(a) make a report in writing of the fact to a Metropolitan Magistrate or a Magistrate of the first`
  line `class having jurisdiction in the place where the said person ordinarily resides; and thereupon the`
  line `provisions of sections 82, 83, 84 and 85 of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), shall`
  line `apply in respect of the said person and his property as if the order directing that he be detained were a`
  line `warrant issued by the Magistrate;`
  line
  line `(b) by order notified in the Official Gazette direct the said person to appear before such officer, at`
  line `such place and within such period as may be specified in the order; and if the said person fails to`
  line `comply with such direction, he shall, unless he proves that it was not possible for him to comply`
  line `therewith and that he had, within the period specified in the order, informed the officer mentioned in`
  line `the order of the reason which rendered compliance therewith impossible and of his whereabouts, be`
  line `punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to one year or with fine or with both.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), every`
  line `offence under clause (b) of sub-section (1) shall be cognisable.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (24813)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 9
  title `Advisory Boards.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00013_197452_1517807319869&sectionId=24813&sectionno=8&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00013_197452_1517807319869
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `For the purposes of sub-clause (a) of clause (4), and sub-clause (c) of`
  line `clause (7), of article 22 of the Constitution,--`
  line
  line `(a) the Central Government and each State Government shall, whenever necessary, constitute one`
  line `or more Advisory Boards each of which shall consist of a Chairman and two other persons possessing`
  line `the qualifications specified in sub-clause (a) of clause (4) of article 22 of the Constitution;`
  line
  line `(b) save as otherwise provided in section 9, the appropriate Government shall, within five weeks`
  line `from the date of detention of a person under a detention order make a reference in respect thereof to`
  line `the Advisory Board constituted under clause (a) to enable the Advisory Board to make the report`
  line `under sub-clause (a) of clause (4) of article 22 of the Constitution;`
  line
  line `(c) the Advisory Board to which a reference is made under clause (b) shall after considering the`
  line `reference and the materials placed before it and after calling for such further information as it may`
  line `deem necessary from the appropriate Government or from any person called for the purpose through`
  line `the appropriate Government or from the person concerned, and if, in any particular case, it considers`
  line `it essential so to do or if the person concerned desires to be heard in person, after hearing him in`
  line `person, prepare its report specifying in a separate paragraph thereof its opinion as to whether or not`
  line `there is sufficient cause for the detention of the person concerned and submit the same within eleven`
  line `weeks from the date of detention of the person concerned;`
  line
  line `(d) when there is a difference of opinion among the members forming the Advisory Board, the`
  line `opinion of the majority of such members shall be deemed to be the opinion of the Board;`
  line
  line `(e) a person against whom an order of detention has been made under this Act shall not be`
  line `entitled to appear by any legal practitioner in any matter connected with the reference to the Advisory`
  line `Board, and the proceedings of the Advisory Board and its report, excepting that part of the report in`
  line `which the opinion of the Advisory Board is specified, shall be confidential;`
  line
  line `(f) in every case where the Advisory Board has reported that there is in its opinion sufficient`
  line `cause for the detention of a person, the appropriate Government may confirm the detention order and`
  line `continue the detention of the person concerned for such period as it thinks fit and in every case where`
  line `the Advisory Board has reported that there is in its opinion no sufficient cause for the detention of the`
  line `person concerned, the appropriate Government shall revoke the detention order and cause the person`
  line `to be released forthwith.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (24814)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 10
  title `Cases in which and circumstances under which persons may be detained for periods longer than three months without obtaining the opinion of Advisory Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00013_197452_1517807319869&sectionId=24814&sectionno=9&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00013_197452_1517807319869
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `^1[9. Cases in which and circumstances under which persons may be detained for periods longer`
  line `than three months without obtaining the opinion of Advisory Board.--(1) Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in this Act, any person (including a foreigner) in respect of whom an order of detention is made`
  line `under this Act at any time before the ^2[31st day of July, 1999], may be detained without obtaining, in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of sub-clause (a) of clause (4) of article 22 of the Constitution, the opinion`
  line `of an Advisory Board for a period longer than three months but not exceeding six months from the date of`
  line `his detention, where the order of detention has been made against such person with a view to preventing`
  line `him from smuggling goods or abetting the smuggling of goods or engaging in transporting or concealing`
  line `or keeping smuggled goods and the Central Government or any officer of the Central Government, not`
  line `below the rank of an Additional Secretary to that Government, specially empowered for the purposes of`
  line `this section by that Government, is satisfied that such person--`
  line
  line `(a) smuggles or is likely to smuggle goods into, out of or through any area highly vulnerable to`
  line `smuggling; or`
  line
  line `(b) abets or is likely to abet the smuggling of goods into, out of or through any area highly`
  line `vulnerable to smuggling; or`
  line
  line `(c) engages or is likely to engage in transporting or concealing or keeping smuggled goods in any`
  line `area highly vulnerable to smuggling,`
  line
  line `and makes a declaration to that effect within five weeks of the detention of such person.`
  line
  line `Explanation1.--In this sub-section, "area highly vulnerable to smuggling" means--`
  line
  line `(i) The Indian customs waters contiguous to ^3[The States of Goa, Gujarat, Karnataka, Kerala,`
  line `Maharashtra and Tamil Nadu and the Union territories of Daman and Diu and Pondicherry];`
  line
  line `(ii) The inland area fifty kilometres in width from the coast of India falling within the territories`
  line `of ^3[the States of Goa, Gujarat, Karnataka, Kerala, Maharashtra and Tamil Nadu and the Union`
  line `territories of Daman and Diu and Pondicherry];`
  line
  line `(iii) the inland area fifty kilometres in width from the India-Pakistan border in the States of`
  line `Gujarat, Jammu and Kashmir, Punjab and Rajasthan;`
  line
  line `(iv) the customs airport of Delhi; and`
  line
  line `(v) such further or other Indian customs waters, or inland area not exceeding one hundred`
  line `kilometres in width from any other coast or border of India, or such other customs station, as the`
  line `Central Government may, having regard to the vulnerability of such waters, area or customs station,`
  line `as the case may be, to smuggling, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify in this behalf.`
  line
  line `Explanation 2.--For the purposes of Explanation 1, "customs airport" and "customs station" shall`
  line `have the same meaning as in clauses (10) and (13) of section 2 of the Customs Act, 1962 (52 of 1962),`
  line respectively.
  line
  line `(2) In the case of any person detained under a detention order to which the provisions of`
  line `sub-section (1) apply, section 8 shall have effect subject to the following modifications, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) in clause (b), for the words "shall, within five weeks", the words "shall, within four months`
  line `and two weeks" shall be substituted;`
  line
  line `(ii) in clause (c),--`
  line
  line `(1) for the words "the detention of the person concerned", the words "the continued detention`
  line `of the person concerned" shall be substituted;`
  line
  line `(2) for the words "eleven weeks", the words "five months and three weeks" shall be`
  line substituted;
  line `(iii) in clause (f), for the words "for the detention", at both the places where they occur, the words`
  line `"for the continued detention" shall be substituted.]`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 58 of 1984, s. 2, for section 9 (w.e.f. 13-7-1984).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 15 of 1996, s. 2, for "31st day of July, 1996" (w.e.f. 31-7-1996).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 23 of 1987, s. 2, for certain words (w.e.f. 2-7-1987).`
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (24815)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 11
  title `Maximum period of detention.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00013_197452_1517807319869&sectionId=24815&sectionno=10&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00013_197452_1517807319869
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `The maximum period for which any person may be detained in`
  line `pursuance of any detention order to which the provisions of section 9 do not apply and which has been`
  line `confirmed under clause (f) of section 8 shall be ^1[a period of one year from the date of detention or the`
  line `specified period, whichever period expires later] and the maximum period for which any person may be`
  line `detained in pursuance of any detention order to which the provisions of section 9 apply and which has`
  line `been confirmed under clause (f) of section 8 read with sub-section (2) of section 9 shall be ^2[a period of`
  line `two years from the date of detention or the specified period, whichever period expires later]:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this section shall affect the power of the appropriate Government`
  line `in either case to revoke or modify the detention order at any earlier time.`
  line
  line `^3[Explanation.--In this section and in section 10A, "specified period" means the period during which`
  line `the Proclamation of Emergency issued under clause (1) of article 352 of the Constitution on the 3rd day of`
  line `December, 1971 and the Proclamation of Emergency issued under that clause on the 25th day of June,`
  line `1975, are both in operation.]`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 20 of 1976, s. 3, for "one year from the date of detention" (w.e.f. 12-12-1975).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for "two years from the date of detention" (w.e.f. 12-12-1975).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 20 of 1976, s. 3 (w.e.f. 12-12-1975).`
obj_root_law_sections_10_a:
  sectionId (24816)
  sectionNo 10A
  orderNo 12
  title `Extension of period of detention.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 3, ibid. (w.e.f. 12-12-1975).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00013_197452_1517807319869&sectionId=24816&sectionno=10A&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00013_197452_1517807319869
obj_root_law_sections_10_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[10A. Extension of period of detention.--(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other`
  line `provision of this Act, the detention of every person detained under a detention order which has been`
  line `confirmed under clause (f) of section 8 before the commencement of the Conservation of Foreign`
  line `Exchange and Prevention of Smuggling Activities (Amendment) Act, 1976, and which is in force`
  line `immediately before such commencement shall, unless his detention has been continued by the appropriate`
  line `Government under the said clause for a period shorter than one year from the date of his detention,`
  line `continue until the expiry of a period of one year from the date of his detention under such order or until`
  line `the expiry of the specified period, whichever period expires later:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall affect the power of the appropriate`
  line `Government to revoke or modify such detention order at any earlier time.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other provision of this Act, the detention of every`
  line `person detained under a detention order which has been confirmed under clause (f) of section 8 read with`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 9 before the commencement of the Conservation of Foreign Exchange and`
  line `Prevention of Smuggling Activities (Amendment) Act, 1976, and which is in force immediately before`
  line `such commencement, shall, unless his detention has been continued by the appropriate Government under`
  line `the said clause (f) read with the said sub-section (2), for a period shorter than two years from the date of`
  line `his detention, continue until the expiry of a period of two years from the date of his detention under such`
  line `order or until the expiry of the specified period, whichever period expires later:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall affect the power of the appropriate`
  line `Government to revoke or modify such detention order at any earlier time.]`
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (24817)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 13
  title `Revocation of detention orders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00013_197452_1517807319869&sectionId=24817&sectionno=11&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00013_197452_1517807319869
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) Without prejudice to the provisions of section 21 of the`
  line `General Clauses Act, 1897 (10 of 1897), a detention order may, at any time, be revoked or modified--`
  line
  line `(a) notwithstanding that the order has been made by an officer of a State Government, by that`
  line `State Government or by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(b) notwithstanding that the order has been made by an officer of the Central Government or by a`
  line `State Government, by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The revocation of a detention order shall not bar the making of another detention order under`
  line `section 3 against the same person.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (24818)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 14
  title `Temporary release of persons detained.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00013_197452_1517807319869&sectionId=24818&sectionno=12&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00013_197452_1517807319869
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) The Central Government may, at any time,`
  line `direct that any person detained in pursuance of a detention order made by that Government or an officer`
  line `subordinate to that Government or by a State Government or by an officer subordinate to a State`
  line `Government, may be released for any specified period either without conditions or upon such conditions`
  line `specified in the direction as that person accepts, and may, at any time, cancel his release.`
  line
  line `(1A) A State Government may, at any time, direct that any person detained in pursuance of a`
  line `detention order made by that Government or by an officer subordinate to that Government may be`
  line `released for any specified period either without conditions or upon such conditions specified in the`
  line `direction as that person accepts, and may, at any time, cancel his release.]`
  line
  line `(2) In directing the release of any person ^2[under sub-section (1) or sub-section (1A), the Government`
  line `directing the release] may require him to enter into a bond with sureties for the due observance of the`
  line `conditions specified in the direction.`
  line
  line `(3) Any person released under ^3[sub-section (1) or sub-section (1A)] shall surrender himself at the`
  line `time and place, and to the authority, specified in the order directing his release or cancelling his release,`
  line `as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(4) If any person fails without sufficient cause to surrender himself in the manner specified in`
  line `sub-section (3), he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to two years, or`
  line `with fine, or with both.`
  line
  line `(5) If any person released under ^3[sub-section (1) or sub-section (1A)] fails to fulfil any of the`
  line `conditions imposed upon him under the said sub-section or in the bond entered into by him, the bond shall`
  line `be declared to be forfeited and any person bound thereby shall be liable to pay the penalty thereof.`
  line
  line `^4[(6) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law and save as otherwise provided in this`
  line `section, no person against whom a detention order made under this Act is in force shall be released`
  line `whether on bail or bail bond or otherwise.]`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 4, ibid.,for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 12-12-1975).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 20 of 1976, s. 4, for "under sub-section (1), the appropriate Government" (w.e.f. 12-12-1975).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for "sub-section (1)" (w.e.f. 12-12-1975).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 35 of 1975, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-7-1975).`
obj_root_law_sections_12_a:
  sectionId (24819)
  sectionNo 12A
  orderNo 15
  title `Special provisions for dealing with emergency.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00013_197452_1517807319869&sectionId=24819&sectionno=12A&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00013_197452_1517807319869
obj_root_law_sections_12_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[12A. Special provisions for dealing with emergency.--(1) notwithstanding anything contained in`
  line `this Act or any rules of natural justice, the provisions of this section shall have effect during the period of`
  line `operation of the Proclamation of Emergency issued under clause (1) of article 352 of the Constitution on`
  line `the 3rd day of December, 1971, or the Proclamation of Emergency issued under that clause on the 25th`
  line `day of June, 1975, or a period of ^2[twenty-four months] from the 25th day of June, 1975, whichever`
  line `period is the shortest.`
  line
  line `(2) When making an order of detention under this Act against any person after the commencement of`
  line `the Conservation of Foreign Exchange and Prevention of Smuggling Activities (Amendment) Act, 1975`
  line `(35 of 1975), the Central Government or the State Government or, as the case may be, the officer making`
  line `the order of detention shall consider whether the detention of such person under this Act is necessary for`
  line `dealing effectively with the emergency in respect of which the Proclamations referred to in sub-section`
  line `(1) have been issued (hereafter in this section referred to as the emergency) and if, on such consideration,`
  line `the Central Government or the State Government or, as the case may be, the officer is satisfied that it is`
  line `necessary to detain such person for effectively dealing with the emergency, that Government or officer`
  line `may make a declaration to that effect and communicate a copy of the declaration to the person concerned;`
  line
  line `Provided that where such declaration is made by an officer, it shall be reviewed by the appropriate`
  line `Government within fifteen days from the date of making of the declaration and such declaration shall`
  line `cease to have effect unless it is confirmed by that Government, after such review, within the said period`
  line `of fifteen days.`
  line
  line `(3) The question whether the detention of any person in respect of whom a declaration has been made`
  line `under sub-section (2) continues to be necessary for effectively dealing with the emergency shall be`
  line `reconsidered by the appropriate Government within four months from the date of such declaration and`
  line `thereafter at intervals not exceeding four months, and if, on such reconsideration, it appears to the`
  line `appropriate Government that the detention of the person is no longer necessary for effectively dealing`
  line `with the emergency, the Government may revoke the declaration.`
  line
  line `(4) In making any consideration, review or reconsideration under sub-section (2) or (3), the`
  line `appropriate Government or officer may, if such Government or officer considers it to be against the`
  line `public interest to do otherwise, act on the basis of the information and materials in its or his possession`
  line `without disclosing the facts or giving an opportunity of making a representation to the person concerned.`
  line
  line `(5) It shall not be necessary to disclose to any person detained under a detention order to which the`
  line `provisions of sub-section (2) apply, the grounds on which the order has been made during the period the`
  line `declaration made in respect of such person under that sub section is in force, and, accordingly, such`
  line `period shall not be taken into account for the purposes of sub-section (3) of section 3.`
  line
  line `(6) In the case of every person detained under a detention order to which the provisions of`
  line `sub-section (2) apply, being a person in respect of whom a declaration has been made thereunder, the`
  line `period during which such declaration is in force shall not be taken into account for the purpose of`
  line computing--
  line
  line `(i) The periods specified in clauses (b) and (c) of section 8;`
  line
  line `(ii) The periods of "one year" and "five weeks" specified in sub-section (1), the period of "one`
  line
  line `year" specified in sub-section (2)(i), and the period of "six months" specified in sub-section (3) of`
  line `section 9.]`
obj_root_law_sections_12_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by s. 4, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-7-1975).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 90 of 1976, s. 2, for "twelve months" (w.e.f. 16-6-1976).`
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (24820)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 16
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00013_197452_1517807319869&sectionId=24820&sectionno=13&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00013_197452_1517807319869
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `No suit or other legal proceeding shall lie against the`
  line `Central Government or a State Government, and no suit, prosecution or other legal proceedings shall lie`
  line `against any person, for anything in good faith done or intended to be done in pursuance of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (24821)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 17
  title Repeal.
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00013_197452_1517807319869&sectionId=24821&sectionno=14&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00013_197452_1517807319869
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `The Maintenance of Internal Security (Amendment) Ordinance, 1974 (11 of 1974),`
  line `shall, on the commencement of this Act, stand repealed and accordingly the amendments made in the`
  line `Maintenance of Internal Security Act, 1971 (20 of 1971), by the said Ordinance shall, on such`
  line `commencement, cease to have effect.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
